## Hints & warnings
- ClickHouse error code for read-scan overflow is 396 TOO_MANY_ROWS_OR_BYTES; the message text is "Limit for rows or bytes to read exceeded ... (TOO_MANY_ROWS_OR_BYTES)". I matched the name suffix (consistent with the other substring branches). I did NOT verify against a live ClickHouse with a tiny cap -- worth a quick integration check, but the suffix-match mirrors how MEMORY_LIMIT_EXCEEDED/TIMEOUT_EXCEEDED/TOO_SLOW are matched.
- Default OFF on purpose: a row cap affects ALL read queries and could break legit large scans, so it's operator opt-in (same posture as the other CH guards). The weave PR provides the mechanism; core config activates it.
- read_overflow_mode='throw' is the CH default but set explicitly so a future default change can't silently turn this into truncation (which would return wrong/partial results).

## Codebase discoveries
- Settings are module-level constants computed at import; the test suite reloads via importlib.reload (reload_settings fixture) with monkeypatched env.
- merge_default_command_settings / CLICKHOUSE_DEFAULT_COMMAND_SETTINGS = base only -> guards never touch mutations.

